.\" termin.al-name: tail
.\" termin.al-usage: tail [-n count] <path>
.\" termin.al-summary: Print final raw document lines.
.TH TAIL 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
tail \- Print final raw document lines.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
tail [-n count] <path>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads one virtual document as raw text and prints its final newline-separated lines. Paths resolve relative to the current pane directory or from virtual home with
.BR ~ .
The default count is 10.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -n count
Select a non-negative decimal line count from 0 through 1000. The option may precede or follow the single path operand; a later
.B -n
replaces an earlier count.
.SH OUTPUT
Markdown is not rendered. A count of 0 emits an empty text output; a count larger than the document returns all available text lines. A trailing newline is preserved by the raw split-and-join behavior.
.SH FAILURES
Unsupported options, a missing or invalid count, more or fewer than one path, invalid or missing paths, directories, locked files and unavailable documents are rejected. Cancellation returns no output.
.SH LIMITS
The requested count is capped at 1000 lines.
.SH NOTES
The virtual document is read-only and no host filesystem path is accepted.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ tail about.md
$ tail -n 3 ~/changelog.md
$ tail about.md -n 0
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
head(1), cat(1), less(1)
